dataIdInfo.idPurp:
Alaska's commercial fisheries are managed using various regulatory areas (i.e., districts and sections). District and section polygons are delineated based on regulatory descriptions found in 5 AAC 33.200. This data set should NOT be used for navigation or for determining compliance with ADF&G Commercial Fishing Regulations. Please consult the ADF&G Salmon Commercial Fisheries Regulations for the official definitions of regulatory boundaries.
Data last updated June 2023
NOTE: These data attempt to depict boundaries as used for management during a specific time period. In some cases, boundaries used in practice may differ from those described in regulations, reports, maps, and other aids.

scpExt.exDesc: This data quality report applies to the commercial salmon district polygon features and associated attributes published in the PVB_Southeast_Salmon_Districts data set.

dataLineage.statement:
District boundaries were created based on the Alaska Fish and Game Laws and Regulations in ArcGIS Pro.
Southeastern Alaska Area Commercial Salmon Fishing Districts and Sections descriptions were obtained from 5 AAC 33.200
https://www.akleg.gov/basis/aac.asp#5.33.001 Last accessed: May 2023

dataSource.srcDesc:
The base coastline source used is the NHD Flowline line feature class. The NHDFlowline Mean High Water (MHW) coastline data from the National Ocean and Atmospheric Agency (NOAA) that is in the National Hydrography Dataset (NHD). The NHD is available for download here: https://www.usgs.gov/core-science-systems/ngp/national-hydrography/national-hydrography-dataset?qt-science_support_page_related_con=0#qt-science_support_page_related_con
For Mean Low Low Water coastline the Office of Coast Survey Seamless Raster Nautical Chart Services was used to digitize the MLLW line for certain boundaries. The map service can be accessed here: https://nauticalcharts.noaa.gov/data/gis-data-and-services.html#seamless-raster-nautical-chart-services

The U.S./Canada boundary delineation shapefile was downloaded from the International Boundary Commission.
"The shapefile was generated from NAD83 geographic positions of boundary monuments and turning points. Some coordinates are from recent surveys, while most are datum conversion. It is for mapping use only and must not be used to define the boundary. Metadata files are included and are country specific.ï»¿
version 1.3 was downloaded from here: https://www.internationalboundarycommission.org/en/maps-coordinates/coordinates.php

State of Alaska waters (3 nmi boundary) uses NOAA 3nm Baseline REST service accessed below
(https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/arcgis/rest/services/NOAA_Baseline/MapServer/7

Southeastern Alaska Area Commercial Salmon Fishing Districts and Sections descriptions were obtained from 5 AAC 33.200
https://www.akleg.gov/basis/aac.asp#5.33.001 Last accessed: May 2023

prcStep.stepDesc: District boundary coordinates were plotted as points using regulatory decriptions in 5 AAC 33.200. Lines were created from points and used to split district polygons.

NHD coastline line features were converted to polgyons for land features. All GIS data was projected to GCS_1984. Water polygons created from erasing the land features form the basis for the district polygons.
